WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:18.190 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.190 --> 00:00:19.940 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: In
my last conversation

00:00:19.940 --> 00:00:22.640 align:middle line:10%
with Michael Cremo, we discussed
the way in which science

00:00:22.640 --> 00:00:25.700 align:middle line:10%
filters knowledge to
conveniently fit with commonly

00:00:25.700 --> 00:00:29.030 align:middle line:10%
held views, particularly the
religious kind of devotion

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:30.320 align:middle line:10%
to Darwinism.

00:00:30.320 --> 00:00:32.210 align:middle line:10%
In this interview,
we show the evidence

00:00:32.210 --> 00:00:34.630 align:middle line:10%
for the extreme antiquity
of the human race,

00:00:34.630 --> 00:00:36.740 align:middle line:10%
leaving little argument
for the position

00:00:36.740 --> 00:00:39.220 align:middle line:10%
that we evolved
from apes-- no less,

00:00:39.220 --> 00:00:42.574 align:middle line:10%
only a few thousand years ago.

00:00:42.574 --> 00:00:43.990 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
things that came up

00:00:43.990 --> 00:00:47.780 align:middle line:84%
just before we went on today,
Jay Weidner came in and said,

00:00:47.780 --> 00:00:50.040 align:middle line:84%
have you seen this article
that just came out?

00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:52.830 align:middle line:84%
And it says 300 million
year old tooth wheel

00:00:52.830 --> 00:00:57.340 align:middle line:84%
found in Russian coal,
embedded in coal.

00:00:57.340 --> 00:00:59.900 align:middle line:84%
And what was the
original-- well,

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:02.260 align:middle line:84%
right now it's in the
"Huffington Post."

00:01:02.260 --> 00:01:05.110 align:middle line:84%
300 million year old
tool of some kind,

00:01:05.110 --> 00:01:07.300 align:middle line:90%
it was a gear of some kind.

00:01:07.300 --> 00:01:10.920 align:middle line:84%
Does that fit at all
within your understanding

00:01:10.920 --> 00:01:13.830 align:middle line:90%
of our human antiquity?

00:01:13.830 --> 00:01:16.450 align:middle line:10%
>>MICHAEL CREMO: Yes, it does.

00:01:16.450 --> 00:01:19.200 align:middle line:10%
I think humans have been
present for hundreds

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:21.120 align:middle line:10%
of millions of years on Earth.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:23.080 align:middle line:10%
And there are other
discoveries that

00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:26.700 align:middle line:10%
are consistent with
this most recently

00:01:26.700 --> 00:01:28.457 align:middle line:10%
reported one from Russia.

00:01:28.457 --> 00:01:30.540 align:middle line:84%
Of course, these things
always need further study.

00:01:30.540 --> 00:01:31.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:01:31.290 --> 00:01:35.690 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: But there are, in
the scientific literature,

00:01:35.690 --> 00:01:38.810 align:middle line:84%
reports of discoveries that
are consistent with this.

00:01:38.810 --> 00:01:44.400 align:middle line:84%
For example, in the year
1862, a scientific journal

00:01:44.400 --> 00:01:48.860 align:middle line:84%
called "The Geologist"
published an interesting report.

00:01:48.860 --> 00:01:53.220 align:middle line:84%
A human skeleton was found
90 feet below the surface

00:01:53.220 --> 00:01:58.360 align:middle line:84%
of the ground in Macoupin
County in the state of Illinois

00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:01.300 align:middle line:90%
in the United States.

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:05.140 align:middle line:84%
And we got in touch
with geologists

00:02:05.140 --> 00:02:07.600 align:middle line:84%
of the State Geological
Survey of Illinois.

00:02:07.600 --> 00:02:11.940 align:middle line:84%
And we asked them how
old is the formation

00:02:11.940 --> 00:02:14.770 align:middle line:90%
at that level at that place?

00:02:14.770 --> 00:02:20.450 align:middle line:84%
And they said about
300 million years.

00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:25.100 align:middle line:84%
So that's consistent with
this recent report from Russia

00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:29.650 align:middle line:84%
of this aluminum object,
gear-shaped object, that

00:02:29.650 --> 00:02:32.990 align:middle line:84%
was found in coal
deposits of Vladivostok

00:02:32.990 --> 00:02:36.260 align:middle line:90%
in Far Eastern Russia.

00:02:36.260 --> 00:02:40.620 align:middle line:84%
And there are reports
from the same time period.

00:02:40.620 --> 00:02:49.050 align:middle line:84%
In the year 1892, a woman
named Mrs. Robert Culp

00:02:49.050 --> 00:02:54.550 align:middle line:84%
was putting a piece of coal
into a coal burning stove.

00:02:54.550 --> 00:02:57.965 align:middle line:84%
And it was a big piece of
coal, so she broke it in half.

00:02:57.965 --> 00:03:03.432 align:middle line:84%
And inside she found a gold
chain about 10 inches long.

00:03:03.432 --> 00:03:04.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A gold chain?

00:03:04.390 --> 00:03:04.931 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes.

00:03:04.931 --> 00:03:07.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, real,
sophisticated little gold

00:03:07.590 --> 00:03:08.220 align:middle line:90%
links?

00:03:08.220 --> 00:03:09.808 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:03:09.808 --> 00:03:16.070 align:middle line:84%
And we were able to get from
the report the name of the mine

00:03:16.070 --> 00:03:19.210 align:middle line:90%
that this object came from.

00:03:19.210 --> 00:03:24.690 align:middle line:84%
And we asked geologists how
old is the coal in that mine?

00:03:24.690 --> 00:03:30.250 align:middle line:84%
And again, they said
about 300 million years.

00:03:30.250 --> 00:03:32.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is a vast
expanse between these two

00:03:32.490 --> 00:03:36.660 align:middle line:90%
places, Vladivostok and England.

00:03:36.660 --> 00:03:39.350 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Well, this would
be from the United States,

00:03:39.350 --> 00:03:40.780 align:middle line:90%
from the state of Illinois.

00:03:40.780 --> 00:03:42.495 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, this one was
from the state of Illinois.

00:03:42.495 --> 00:03:42.760 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Right.

00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:43.676 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, got you.

00:03:43.676 --> 00:03:44.967 align:middle line:90%
Even more vast reach.

00:03:44.967 --> 00:03:45.550 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:03:45.550 --> 00:03:45.920 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:03:45.920 --> 00:03:47.586 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And then
there was another case

00:03:47.586 --> 00:03:51.480 align:middle line:84%
of a gold thread being
found in England.

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:53.940 align:middle line:84%
That was reported in
an English newspaper

00:03:53.940 --> 00:03:55.430 align:middle line:90%
from the 19th century.

00:03:55.430 --> 00:04:00.570 align:middle line:84%
And that, again, was about
from the same time period.

00:04:00.570 --> 00:04:05.010 align:middle line:84%
So they're very
interesting discoveries.

00:04:05.010 --> 00:04:08.520 align:middle line:84%
They completely
contradict everything

00:04:08.520 --> 00:04:12.215 align:middle line:84%
that most scientists now
think about human origin.

00:04:12.215 --> 00:04:12.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:04:12.840 --> 00:04:15.340 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to get into
many, many more of these.

00:04:15.340 --> 00:04:20.370 align:middle line:84%
However, when we look at it
from kind of a classical,

00:04:20.370 --> 00:04:22.340 align:middle line:84%
as it's taught now,
archaeological point

00:04:22.340 --> 00:04:26.130 align:middle line:84%
of view, what would be said of
what was going on on the Earth

00:04:26.130 --> 00:04:27.530 align:middle line:90%
300 million years ago?

00:04:27.530 --> 00:04:30.230 align:middle line:90%
What would that depiction be?

00:04:30.230 --> 00:04:33.940 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Well, according to
the classical understanding,

00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:37.430 align:middle line:84%
that would be during the
Carboniferous period.

00:04:37.430 --> 00:04:40.890 align:middle line:84%
And they would say
at that time there

00:04:40.890 --> 00:04:46.070 align:middle line:84%
were jungles of
gymnosperm plants.

00:04:46.070 --> 00:04:50.720 align:middle line:84%
And gymnosperm means not of
the flowering plant family,

00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:53.060 align:middle line:84%
in other words,
things like ferns

00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:57.230 align:middle line:84%
and other types of
plants of that nature.

00:04:57.230 --> 00:04:59.730 align:middle line:84%
And there would have
been amphibians.

00:04:59.730 --> 00:05:01.330 align:middle line:84%
This would be from
before the time

00:05:01.330 --> 00:05:04.580 align:middle line:84%
of the dinosaurs,
certainly no human life

00:05:04.580 --> 00:05:06.700 align:middle line:84%
according to the standard
picture of things.

00:05:06.700 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:84%
Just various types of amphibians
and plants on the Earth.

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:16.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we're looking
at a huge discretion

00:05:16.200 --> 00:05:18.820 align:middle line:84%
here in terms of what
was actually populating

00:05:18.820 --> 00:05:21.000 align:middle line:84%
the planet 300
million years ago.

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:24.320 align:middle line:84%
If we have something
capable, a human,

00:05:24.320 --> 00:05:27.630 align:middle line:84%
capable of creating an
instrument of some kind,

00:05:27.630 --> 00:05:30.760 align:middle line:84%
a tool of some kind-- they
say it's a tooth wheel?

00:05:30.760 --> 00:05:31.620 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:05:31.620 --> 00:05:34.020 align:middle line:84%
It's like a gear
box of some kind?

00:05:34.020 --> 00:05:35.810 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Well,
actually it's a bar,

00:05:35.810 --> 00:05:38.900 align:middle line:84%
it's a bar-shaped
structure that has

00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:48.340 align:middle line:84%
what appear to be gears on
it that-- You know, they--

00:05:48.340 --> 00:05:52.670 align:middle line:84%
In different types of machines
that we have today, there

00:05:52.670 --> 00:05:58.640 align:middle line:84%
are these gear bars that
operate in connection with gear

00:05:58.640 --> 00:06:00.780 align:middle line:84%
wheels that are
part of machines.

00:06:00.780 --> 00:06:01.714 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:06:01.714 --> 00:06:02.650 align:middle line:90%
So, yeah.

00:06:02.650 --> 00:06:07.480 align:middle line:84%
So that existed, a finally
fabricated gold chain

00:06:07.480 --> 00:06:10.570 align:middle line:90%
existed 300 million years ago.

00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:13.070 align:middle line:90%
We do have a huge discrepancy.

00:06:13.070 --> 00:06:15.524 align:middle line:84%
And you studied
this from a couple

00:06:15.524 --> 00:06:16.690 align:middle line:90%
of different points of view.

00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:19.390 align:middle line:84%
You've done a vast amount
of research as documented

00:06:19.390 --> 00:06:21.900 align:middle line:84%
in your book, "Forbidden
Archeology," which

00:06:21.900 --> 00:06:25.350 align:middle line:84%
is more than 900 pages
of evidence for this.

00:06:25.350 --> 00:06:29.610 align:middle line:84%
In addition, you
are also a devotee

00:06:29.610 --> 00:06:32.590 align:middle line:84%
of an aspect of the
Vedas that talks

00:06:32.590 --> 00:06:35.260 align:middle line:84%
about the large, long
cycles of history

00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:39.060 align:middle line:84%
where human beings are
wiped out or somehow,

00:06:39.060 --> 00:06:41.850 align:middle line:84%
whether it's a cataclysm
or what, disappear,

00:06:41.850 --> 00:06:45.140 align:middle line:84%
re-evolve-- not evolve--
reappear with their knowledge

00:06:45.140 --> 00:06:46.180 align:middle line:90%
intact apparently.

00:06:46.180 --> 00:06:49.190 align:middle line:84%
And this keeps on and
on and on for how long?

00:06:49.190 --> 00:06:53.570 align:middle line:84%
Over what span of
time would the Puranas

00:06:53.570 --> 00:06:56.520 align:middle line:90%
say humankind has been here?

00:06:56.520 --> 00:07:03.600 align:middle line:84%
They would say that humans
have appeared and reappeared

00:07:03.600 --> 00:07:06.380 align:middle line:84%
in the course of
vast cycles of time.

00:07:06.380 --> 00:07:08.380 align:middle line:84%
The basic unit of
this cyclical time

00:07:08.380 --> 00:07:11.690 align:middle line:84%
is called the kalpa or the
Day of the Brahma, which

00:07:11.690 --> 00:07:15.797 align:middle line:90%
lasts about 4 billion years.

00:07:15.797 --> 00:07:17.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we discussed
that a little bit

00:07:17.630 --> 00:07:18.970 align:middle line:90%
in our last conversation.

00:07:18.970 --> 00:07:21.860 align:middle line:84%
How many of those cycles
have there already been?

00:07:21.860 --> 00:07:24.990 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Endless
numbers of them.

00:07:24.990 --> 00:07:27.419 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we could have
been there trillions of years?

00:07:27.419 --> 00:07:27.960 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes.

00:07:27.960 --> 00:07:34.210 align:middle line:84%
But according to the current
kalpa, the most recent creation

00:07:34.210 --> 00:07:36.350 align:middle line:84%
or manifestation
of that, we would

00:07:36.350 --> 00:07:43.220 align:middle line:84%
expect to find evidence for a
human presence going back say,

00:07:43.220 --> 00:07:47.110 align:middle line:90%
about 2 billion years roughly.

00:07:47.110 --> 00:07:53.790 align:middle line:84%
And before that, it would be
like if you had a computer disk

00:07:53.790 --> 00:07:56.924 align:middle line:84%
and you wiped out
the evidence on it.

00:07:56.924 --> 00:07:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:07:57.590 --> 00:08:00.170 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: You know, that's what
happens at the end of a kalpa.

00:08:00.170 --> 00:08:08.080 align:middle line:84%
It's like whatever is there in
the material manifestation just

00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:12.320 align:middle line:84%
gets wiped away, so that
you have a clean disk.

00:08:12.320 --> 00:08:16.210 align:middle line:84%
So when the next kalpa
or creation event comes,

00:08:16.210 --> 00:08:18.326 align:middle line:90%
it gets written on again.

00:08:18.326 --> 00:08:20.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's why
you wouldn't find evidence

00:08:20.450 --> 00:08:24.360 align:middle line:84%
that would necessarily date back
into the hundreds of billions

00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:26.970 align:middle line:84%
or trillions of years even if
you had the instrumentation

00:08:26.970 --> 00:08:27.470 align:middle line:90%
to do that.

00:08:27.470 --> 00:08:28.970 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:08:28.970 --> 00:08:33.900 align:middle line:84%
According to the Veda
cosmology, the universe

00:08:33.900 --> 00:08:37.330 align:middle line:90%
is trillions of years old.

00:08:37.330 --> 00:08:41.659 align:middle line:84%
And it will continue to
exist for trillions of years.

00:08:41.659 --> 00:08:46.620 align:middle line:84%
But at different
times in these cycles,

00:08:46.620 --> 00:08:49.546 align:middle line:90%
things become unmanifest.

00:08:49.546 --> 00:08:52.220 align:middle line:84%
And then they're
manifested again.

00:08:52.220 --> 00:08:55.314 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so the good
news there-- for anybody

00:08:55.314 --> 00:08:56.730 align:middle line:84%
who thought the
world was supposed

00:08:56.730 --> 00:09:00.360 align:middle line:84%
to have ended last month
on December 21, 2012--

00:09:00.360 --> 00:09:02.990 align:middle line:84%
is that from the
Veda perspective,

00:09:02.990 --> 00:09:06.550 align:middle line:84%
we are now only halfway
through the daytime cycle

00:09:06.550 --> 00:09:08.510 align:middle line:84%
of the Day of the
Brahma, which means

00:09:08.510 --> 00:09:11.710 align:middle line:84%
we have another couple billion
years where life flourishes

00:09:11.710 --> 00:09:13.900 align:middle line:84%
and continues to
manifest on Earth.

00:09:13.900 --> 00:09:16.180 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: It's interesting
that you say that.

00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:19.550 align:middle line:84%
Earlier this year, I
was giving some lectures

00:09:19.550 --> 00:09:21.900 align:middle line:90%
at universities in India.

00:09:21.900 --> 00:09:26.210 align:middle line:84%
And one of the questions I
was getting from students

00:09:26.210 --> 00:09:32.280 align:middle line:84%
is is there going to
be doomsday in 2012?

00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:35.430 align:middle line:84%
When I said earlier this
year, I mean earlier in 2012.

00:09:35.430 --> 00:09:36.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:38.660 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Earlier last
year, early in last year

00:09:38.660 --> 00:09:41.930 align:middle line:84%
I was giving some lectures
at universities in India.

00:09:41.930 --> 00:09:43.720 align:middle line:84%
And that was one of
the common questions

00:09:43.720 --> 00:09:45.290 align:middle line:90%
I was getting from students.

00:09:45.290 --> 00:09:51.172 align:middle line:84%
Because in India, they had
been playing this movie "2012"

00:09:51.172 --> 00:09:51.984 align:middle line:90%
on all--

00:09:51.984 --> 00:09:52.734 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, god.

00:09:52.734 --> 00:09:54.030 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: --the cable channels.

00:09:54.030 --> 00:09:54.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's horrible.

00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:56.430 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And there's
this one image

00:09:56.430 --> 00:10:00.485 align:middle line:84%
where this huge tidal wave
comes washing over India

00:10:00.485 --> 00:10:02.515 align:middle line:90%
up into the Himalayan Mountains.

00:10:02.515 --> 00:10:04.379 align:middle line:84%
And there's a monk
up there, you know--

00:10:04.379 --> 00:10:05.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Which is awful.

