>>CREMO: --watching this
huge tidal wave coming.

00:10:08.526 --> 00:10:11.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You assured them
in your tradition, no.

00:10:11.930 --> 00:10:12.827 align:middle line:90%
We're fine--

00:10:12.827 --> 00:10:13.410 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:10:13.410 --> 00:10:14.356 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --for
another couple billion.

00:10:14.356 --> 00:10:15.772 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Yeah, so
you can register

00:10:15.772 --> 00:10:16.780 align:middle line:90%
for next year's classes.

00:10:16.780 --> 00:10:18.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You got 2 more
billion in the cycle.

00:10:18.470 --> 00:10:18.800 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:19.633 align:middle line:90%
We've got some time.

00:10:19.633 --> 00:10:21.630 align:middle line:84%
It's going to happen,
but not anytime soon.

00:10:21.630 --> 00:10:22.171 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:10:22.171 --> 00:10:24.274 align:middle line:90%
OK, now going back.

00:10:24.274 --> 00:10:25.940 align:middle line:84%
When we talked last
time, we were really

00:10:25.940 --> 00:10:29.150 align:middle line:84%
setting a case of why
knowledge is filtered,

00:10:29.150 --> 00:10:32.480 align:middle line:84%
and that there is a larger kind
of agenda that really feeds

00:10:32.480 --> 00:10:35.910 align:middle line:84%
into a materialistic view of
life, which leads to ultimately

00:10:35.910 --> 00:10:39.710 align:middle line:84%
consumerism, which has its
devastating consequences if we

00:10:39.710 --> 00:10:41.630 align:middle line:84%
overconsume, which of
course we are doing.

00:10:41.630 --> 00:10:42.130 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:10:42.130 --> 00:10:44.277 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I'm just trying
to put it in a nutshell.

00:10:44.277 --> 00:10:44.860 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Sure.

00:10:44.860 --> 00:10:50.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so when we
talked about your early past,

00:10:50.490 --> 00:10:54.670 align:middle line:84%
you were of a mind that you
wanted to find evidence.

00:10:54.670 --> 00:10:58.250 align:middle line:84%
If you were reading these
ancient Vedic texts that

00:10:58.250 --> 00:11:00.490 align:middle line:84%
were talking about
this extreme antiquity,

00:11:00.490 --> 00:11:03.660 align:middle line:84%
your hypothesis is there
has to be evidence for it.

00:11:03.660 --> 00:11:06.200 align:middle line:84%
And so you set out to
find it, and you did.

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:08.660 align:middle line:84%
And so in this
conversation, I'd really

00:11:08.660 --> 00:11:12.240 align:middle line:84%
like to talk about the time in
which some of these discoveries

00:11:12.240 --> 00:11:13.150 align:middle line:90%
were made.

00:11:13.150 --> 00:11:16.200 align:middle line:84%
This whole period of the
early 20th century, I mean,

00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:19.670 align:middle line:84%
it was an explosion of
experimentation and discovery

00:11:19.670 --> 00:11:20.470 align:middle line:90%
of all kinds.

00:11:20.470 --> 00:11:25.570 align:middle line:84%
It seemed to shut down
by mid-20th century.

00:11:25.570 --> 00:11:28.860 align:middle line:84%
Late 19th, early 20th
century, all kinds

00:11:28.860 --> 00:11:32.370 align:middle line:84%
of things we being discovered
on a spiritual level

00:11:32.370 --> 00:11:34.710 align:middle line:90%
and on a material level.

00:11:34.710 --> 00:11:36.570 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Yeah, you're
right about that.

00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:40.200 align:middle line:84%
A lot of the
archaeological evidence

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:44.780 align:middle line:84%
for extreme human antiquity
was being publicly reported

00:11:44.780 --> 00:11:48.820 align:middle line:84%
by scientists in the late 19th
century and early 20th century.

00:11:48.820 --> 00:11:51.840 align:middle line:90%


00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:54.830 align:middle line:84%
And also, when we look at
alternative explanations

00:11:54.830 --> 00:11:59.090 align:middle line:84%
for human origins that involve
some kind of spiritual element,

00:11:59.090 --> 00:12:02.430 align:middle line:84%
we see that a lot of
prominent scientists

00:12:02.430 --> 00:12:05.880 align:middle line:84%
were conducting research
into the paranormal

00:12:05.880 --> 00:12:08.140 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:12:08.140 --> 00:12:12.280 align:middle line:84%
And I think there were
a couple of reasons

00:12:12.280 --> 00:12:19.280 align:middle line:84%
why that kind of research
stopped being publicly reported

00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:22.010 align:middle line:90%
by prominent scientists.

00:12:22.010 --> 00:12:29.910 align:middle line:84%
And one reason is that, in terms
of the archaeological evidence

00:12:29.910 --> 00:12:32.520 align:middle line:84%
for extreme human
antiquity, before that time,

00:12:32.520 --> 00:12:37.640 align:middle line:84%
they really didn't have
their timeline totally fixed.

00:12:37.640 --> 00:12:39.810 align:middle line:84%
As a result of some
discoveries that

00:12:39.810 --> 00:12:43.420 align:middle line:84%
were made in the
late 19th century,

00:12:43.420 --> 00:12:48.100 align:middle line:84%
they fixed their timeline so
that they would have humans

00:12:48.100 --> 00:12:51.500 align:middle line:84%
like us appearing
less than a couple

00:12:51.500 --> 00:12:53.850 align:middle line:90%
hundred thousand years ago.

00:12:53.850 --> 00:12:54.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:12:54.600 --> 00:12:57.330 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And then, because
they had fixed their timeline

00:12:57.330 --> 00:13:03.660 align:middle line:84%
in that way, then they dismissed
all these earlier discoveries

00:13:03.660 --> 00:13:08.070 align:middle line:84%
that had shown human beings were
existing for far longer periods

00:13:08.070 --> 00:13:13.340 align:middle line:84%
of time going back many
millions of years even.

00:13:13.340 --> 00:13:15.220 align:middle line:84%
Because they were
saying, well, if humans

00:13:15.220 --> 00:13:20.080 align:middle line:84%
like us appeared less
than 200,000 years ago,

00:13:20.080 --> 00:13:25.790 align:middle line:84%
then these other discoveries
couldn't possibly be true.

00:13:25.790 --> 00:13:28.290 align:middle line:90%
So let's forget about them.

00:13:28.290 --> 00:13:30.560 align:middle line:90%
And they were forgotten.

00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And in terms of the alternative
explanations of human origins

00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:41.920 align:middle line:84%
that involve what we might
call paranormal elements,

00:13:41.920 --> 00:13:45.220 align:middle line:84%
there were scientists who were
investigating these things,

00:13:45.220 --> 00:13:50.260 align:middle line:84%
but they also stopped publicly
reporting these things

00:13:50.260 --> 00:13:53.500 align:middle line:90%
in the early 20th century.

00:13:53.500 --> 00:14:00.550 align:middle line:84%
And I think there are
some reasons for this.

00:14:00.550 --> 00:14:07.200 align:middle line:84%
And one reason was that
governments and corporations

00:14:07.200 --> 00:14:10.160 align:middle line:84%
started putting huge
amounts of money

00:14:10.160 --> 00:14:14.400 align:middle line:84%
into science around the
time of World War I.

00:14:14.400 --> 00:14:23.700 align:middle line:84%
And they wanted results from
their investment in science.

00:14:23.700 --> 00:14:25.930 align:middle line:84%
They wanted very
specific things.

00:14:25.930 --> 00:14:28.220 align:middle line:90%
They wanted weapons.

00:14:28.220 --> 00:14:30.880 align:middle line:90%
They wanted pharmaceuticals.

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:34.450 align:middle line:90%
They wanted consumer products.

00:14:34.450 --> 00:14:40.270 align:middle line:84%
And scientists
decided, well, if we

00:14:40.270 --> 00:14:44.210 align:middle line:84%
want all this money,
billions of dollars,

00:14:44.210 --> 00:14:47.230 align:middle line:84%
that corporations
and governments are

00:14:47.230 --> 00:14:52.230 align:middle line:84%
prepared to give us,
we should kind of

00:14:52.230 --> 00:14:58.125 align:middle line:84%
limit our scientific activity
to things that further those--

00:14:58.125 --> 00:14:59.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Economic agendas.

00:14:59.250 --> 00:15:02.610 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: --particular goals.

00:15:02.610 --> 00:15:05.030 align:middle line:84%
And therefore,
they decided, well,

00:15:05.030 --> 00:15:08.520 align:middle line:84%
all this paranormal
research and things

00:15:08.520 --> 00:15:12.330 align:middle line:84%
of that, that isn't really
contributing to that.

00:15:12.330 --> 00:15:17.970 align:middle line:84%
So let's focus on the
strictly material things.

00:15:17.970 --> 00:15:20.730 align:middle line:84%
And in a sense,
that was productive

00:15:20.730 --> 00:15:27.930 align:middle line:84%
because they did get a
lot of influence, because

00:15:27.930 --> 00:15:31.290 align:middle line:84%
of the huge investments that
government and corporations

00:15:31.290 --> 00:15:36.220 align:middle line:84%
made in science that
would give weapons,

00:15:36.220 --> 00:15:40.040 align:middle line:84%
that would give
pharmaceuticals, that

00:15:40.040 --> 00:15:43.400 align:middle line:90%
would give consumer products.

00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:46.760 align:middle line:90%
But there was a cost to that.

00:15:46.760 --> 00:15:48.930 align:middle line:84%
And I think we're
still suffering

00:15:48.930 --> 00:15:53.890 align:middle line:84%
the effects of that bargain
that was made at that time.

00:15:53.890 --> 00:15:58.690 align:middle line:84%
Because what we wind up with
is an incomplete picture

00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:04.400 align:middle line:84%
of reality that leaves
out the spiritual element.

00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:06.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Everything
non-physical.

00:16:06.350 --> 00:16:06.940 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:16:06.940 --> 00:16:11.150 align:middle line:84%
Because of that, I think we've
got an environmental crisis.

00:16:11.150 --> 00:16:14.240 align:middle line:84%
We've got a financial
crisis, and we've

00:16:14.240 --> 00:16:20.120 align:middle line:84%
got a political crisis in the
world, intensifying levels

00:16:20.120 --> 00:16:24.010 align:middle line:84%
of conflict that just
don't seem to go away

00:16:24.010 --> 00:16:27.751 align:middle line:90%
no matter how hard we try.

00:16:27.751 --> 00:16:29.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And then, when you--

00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:31.100 align:middle line:84%
And it's not only
that it seems like it

00:16:31.100 --> 00:16:32.840 align:middle line:84%
was convenient to
be able to develop

00:16:32.840 --> 00:16:34.270 align:middle line:90%
these industries and such.

00:16:34.270 --> 00:16:36.510 align:middle line:84%
But something more
aggressive happened.

00:16:36.510 --> 00:16:39.210 align:middle line:84%
It seems that anything that
wasn't able to be borne out

00:16:39.210 --> 00:16:41.640 align:middle line:84%
in a materialistic
realm of science

00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:44.780 align:middle line:84%
actually was subject to
ridicule from that point

00:16:44.780 --> 00:16:46.040 align:middle line:90%
forward as well.

00:16:46.040 --> 00:16:47.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it wasn't
just that we need

00:16:47.520 --> 00:16:49.100 align:middle line:90%
to focus on this for a while.

00:16:49.100 --> 00:16:51.130 align:middle line:84%
There was almost
a direct attempt

00:16:51.130 --> 00:16:54.150 align:middle line:84%
to kill the other types
of research and science,

00:16:54.150 --> 00:16:57.160 align:middle line:84%
where it just sort
of disappeared.

00:16:57.160 --> 00:16:59.660 align:middle line:84%
for decades, as
a matter of fact,

00:16:59.660 --> 00:17:02.690 align:middle line:84%
till some of the scientists of
the more modern era from '70s

00:17:02.690 --> 00:17:04.650 align:middle line:84%
forward started really
researching into it

00:17:04.650 --> 00:17:06.477 align:middle line:90%
again at universities even.

00:17:06.477 --> 00:17:07.060 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:17:07.060 --> 00:17:12.670 align:middle line:84%
And not only did they
ridicule people at the time,

00:17:12.670 --> 00:17:18.579 align:middle line:84%
but they rewrote the
whole history of science.

00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:23.579 align:middle line:84%
For example, if you look
in any physics textbook

00:17:23.579 --> 00:17:29.600 align:middle line:84%
today, you'll see descriptions
of the work of Pierre and Marie

00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:33.700 align:middle line:84%
Curie, who were
husband and wife.

00:17:33.700 --> 00:17:37.060 align:middle line:84%
They both got Nobel
Prizes for their work

00:17:37.060 --> 00:17:39.440 align:middle line:84%
in discovering radium
and doing a lot

00:17:39.440 --> 00:17:45.320 align:middle line:84%
of the early research
in radioactivity.

00:17:45.320 --> 00:17:47.620 align:middle line:84%
And you'll read about
that in the textbooks.

00:17:47.620 --> 00:17:52.330 align:middle line:84%
But what you won't read about
is the years of research

00:17:52.330 --> 00:17:58.327 align:middle line:84%
they did with psychics,
people with paranormal powers.

00:17:58.327 --> 00:17:59.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean,
that's real science,

00:17:59.910 --> 00:18:02.970 align:middle line:84%
where you're willing to
look into all realms.

00:18:02.970 --> 00:18:05.970 align:middle line:84%
It's not just exclusive
to one or the other.

00:18:05.970 --> 00:18:08.499 align:middle line:84%
And they did this for quite
a long time, didn't they?

00:18:08.499 --> 00:18:09.040 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes.

00:18:09.040 --> 00:18:14.850 align:middle line:84%
They did two years of research
with a medium, an Italian lady

00:18:14.850 --> 00:18:17.460 align:middle line:90%
named Eusapia Palladino.

00:18:17.460 --> 00:18:20.220 align:middle line:84%
And this woman had some
psychokinetic abilities,

00:18:20.220 --> 00:18:24.830 align:middle line:84%
mind over matter abilities,
that they wanted to test.

00:18:24.830 --> 00:18:30.910 align:middle line:84%
And they thought these ideas
were relevant to physics.

00:18:30.910 --> 00:18:34.740 align:middle line:84%
And they were part
of a group of 20

00:18:34.740 --> 00:18:37.520 align:middle line:84%
prominent European
scientists who

00:18:37.520 --> 00:18:42.130 align:middle line:84%
were conducting these
experiments with this medium

00:18:42.130 --> 00:18:46.470 align:middle line:84%
in Paris early in
the 20th century.

00:18:46.470 --> 00:18:51.260 align:middle line:84%
And they got tremendous
results on one occasion.

00:18:51.260 --> 00:18:54.050 align:middle line:84%
They were sitting
with the medium

00:18:54.050 --> 00:18:58.900 align:middle line:84%
in the laboratory of
the Psychology Institute

00:18:58.900 --> 00:19:01.870 align:middle line:90%
in Paris in broad daylight.

00:19:01.870 --> 00:19:04.790 align:middle line:84%
And the medium was
sitting in a chair.

00:19:04.790 --> 00:19:07.360 align:middle line:84%
Marie Curie was
holding her hands.

00:19:07.360 --> 00:19:09.880 align:middle line:84%
Other scientists
were holding her feet

00:19:09.880 --> 00:19:13.350 align:middle line:84%
making sure she
wasn't moving at all.

00:19:13.350 --> 00:19:16.620 align:middle line:84%
And in the middle of the
lab, under what he described

00:19:16.620 --> 00:19:19.830 align:middle line:84%
as perfect conditions
of observation,

00:19:19.830 --> 00:19:23.150 align:middle line:84%
Pierre Curie said a large
table, like this one,

00:19:23.150 --> 00:19:26.360 align:middle line:84%
was floating about 3
feet off the ground.

00:19:26.360 --> 00:19:28.960 align:middle line:84%
And he was measuring how
high it was floating,

00:19:28.960 --> 00:19:31.880 align:middle line:90%
timing how long it was floating.

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:36.380 align:middle line:84%
And after two years of
such results, you know,

00:19:36.380 --> 00:19:38.630 align:middle line:84%
the entire group of
scientists signed

00:19:38.630 --> 00:19:42.300 align:middle line:84%
documents saying these
things are absolutely true.

00:19:42.300 --> 00:19:47.680 align:middle line:84%
Pierre Curie wrote to some of
his prominent physicist friends

00:19:47.680 --> 00:19:52.300 align:middle line:84%
and said, we have to take
these things into account

00:19:52.300 --> 00:20:01.110 align:middle line:84%
if we're going to have a
complete picture of reality.

00:20:01.110 --> 00:20:07.610 align:middle line:84%
But this sort of thing is absent
from the current textbooks

00:20:07.610 --> 00:20:08.570 align:middle line:90%
of physics.

00:20:08.570 --> 00:20:09.445 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:20:09.445 --> 00:20:14.250 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: You'll only find the
work they did with radium.

00:20:14.250 --> 00:20:14.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:20:14.990 --> 00:20:17.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And
therefore, people today

00:20:17.840 --> 00:20:24.260 align:middle line:84%
get an incomplete picture of
what real science actually is.

00:20:24.260 --> 00:20:26.185 align:middle line:84%
When they hear
something like mediums,

00:20:26.185 --> 00:20:30.270 align:middle line:84%
psychokinetic abilities,
they would say,

00:20:30.270 --> 00:20:33.640 align:middle line:84%
this is outside the
bounds of real science.

00:20:33.640 --> 00:20:36.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But they were
using scientific techniques

00:20:36.960 --> 00:20:42.780 align:middle line:84%
and protocols to prove these
things out now 100 years ago.

00:20:42.780 --> 00:20:44.590 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes, they were.

00:20:44.590 --> 00:20:48.925 align:middle line:10%
And I think that
is real science--

00:20:48.925 --> 00:20:49.590 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:20:49.590 --> 00:20:53.390 align:middle line:10%
>>CREMO: --a science that takes
into account everything that's

00:20:53.390 --> 00:20:55.690 align:middle line:10%
possibly true about the
world that we live in.

00:20:55.690 --> 00:21:00.930 align:middle line:10%
And you know, a few years
ago, I was giving a lecture

00:21:00.930 --> 00:21:03.350 align:middle line:10%
at a university of Europe
in the country of Hungary.

00:21:03.350 --> 00:21:06.330 align:middle line:84%
It was their main
science university.

00:21:06.330 --> 00:21:11.100 align:middle line:84%
And I was speaking to
a group of physicists

00:21:11.100 --> 00:21:15.580 align:middle line:84%
and graduate
students of physics.

00:21:15.580 --> 00:21:19.490 align:middle line:84%
And I was going through what
I call the hidden history

00:21:19.490 --> 00:21:23.870 align:middle line:84%
of physics, the accounts
of great physicists,

00:21:23.870 --> 00:21:32.210 align:middle line:84%
like the Curies, who had done
research in these fields that

00:21:32.210 --> 00:21:36.270 align:middle line:84%
are now considered outside
the bounds of real physics

00:21:36.270 --> 00:21:38.030 align:middle line:90%
or science.

00:21:38.030 --> 00:21:43.170 align:middle line:84%
And I was wondering what
they were going to say.

00:21:43.170 --> 00:21:47.990 align:middle line:84%
So afterwards, one of the
physicists came up to me

00:21:47.990 --> 00:21:52.440 align:middle line:84%
and said, you know, I'm glad
that you gave this talk.

00:21:52.440 --> 00:21:55.370 align:middle line:84%
By day, I'm doing
plasma physics,

00:21:55.370 --> 00:21:58.350 align:middle line:84%
the physics of
superheated gases.

00:21:58.350 --> 00:22:02.010 align:middle line:84%
But he told me,
privately at night, I'm

00:22:02.010 --> 00:22:05.060 align:middle line:84%
doing some experiments
in telepathy.

00:22:05.060 --> 00:22:09.660 align:middle line:90%
He told me, I have a son.

00:22:09.660 --> 00:22:11.000 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, he's young.

00:22:11.000 --> 00:22:12.390 align:middle line:90%
And I put him in another room.

00:22:12.390 --> 00:22:14.100 align:middle line:84%
And then I flip a
coin, and he's got

00:22:14.100 --> 00:22:16.954 align:middle line:90%
to tell me whether it's heads--

00:22:16.954 --> 00:22:18.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I used to
do that with my son.

00:22:18.620 --> 00:22:18.920 align:middle line:90%
Tails.

00:22:18.920 --> 00:22:19.710 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: --or tails.

00:22:19.710 --> 00:22:20.335 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:22:20.335 --> 00:22:22.230 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: He said, my
son is getting 80%--

00:22:22.230 --> 00:22:22.855 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:22:22.855 --> 00:22:25.320 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --correct, which
is really unexpected.

00:22:25.320 --> 00:22:26.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Kids are good, yeah.

00:22:26.840 --> 00:22:29.220 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And he said,
I wouldn't tell this

00:22:29.220 --> 00:22:31.240 align:middle line:84%
to any of my colleagues,
because they'd

00:22:31.240 --> 00:22:34.750 align:middle line:84%
think I've gone off
the reservation.

00:22:34.750 --> 00:22:39.360 align:middle line:84%
But he felt safe in
speaking to me about it.

00:22:39.360 --> 00:22:45.300 align:middle line:84%
So this is something
I often encounter,

00:22:45.300 --> 00:22:51.280 align:middle line:84%
that sometimes there're
scientists who, by day, appear

00:22:51.280 --> 00:22:55.720 align:middle line:84%
completely orthodox,
but privately, they

00:22:55.720 --> 00:22:57.236 align:middle line:90%
have other opinions.

00:22:57.236 --> 00:22:57.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, it makes sense.

00:22:57.780 --> 00:22:59.821 align:middle line:84%
If they have an inquiring
mind, why wouldn't they

00:22:59.821 --> 00:23:02.587 align:middle line:84%
want to know a larger
picture, really?

00:23:02.587 --> 00:23:03.170 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Sure.

00:23:03.170 --> 00:23:05.714 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, this dates
back to Sir Isaac Newton.

00:23:05.714 --> 00:23:07.380 align:middle line:84%
I mean, most people
think of him as sort

00:23:07.380 --> 00:23:10.660 align:middle line:84%
of the godfather of the
materialist view of science.

00:23:10.660 --> 00:23:14.230 align:middle line:84%
However, that wasn't his
sole interest at all, was it?

00:23:14.230 --> 00:23:14.730 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: No.

00:23:14.730 --> 00:23:19.310 align:middle line:84%
He actually spent quite a bit
of time researching things

00:23:19.310 --> 00:23:22.890 align:middle line:84%
like alchemy and other
paranormal topics.

00:23:22.890 --> 00:23:26.530 align:middle line:84%
And he wrote
extensively about them.

00:23:26.530 --> 00:23:29.850 align:middle line:84%
This is rarely mentioned
in physics textbooks.

00:23:29.850 --> 00:23:31.990 align:middle line:84%
There are some
historians of science

00:23:31.990 --> 00:23:33.790 align:middle line:90%
who have looked into this.

00:23:33.790 --> 00:23:39.070 align:middle line:84%
But in terms of
scientific discussion

00:23:39.070 --> 00:23:45.100 align:middle line:84%
today, they ignore these aspects
of his work, which I think

00:23:45.100 --> 00:23:45.904 align:middle line:90%
is unfortunate.

00:23:45.904 --> 00:23:46.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is.

00:23:46.570 --> 00:23:47.944 align:middle line:84%
How long have they
been filtering

00:23:47.944 --> 00:23:50.599 align:middle line:90%
that part of his works out?

00:23:50.599 --> 00:23:52.140 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: I would
say the past-- well,

00:23:52.140 --> 00:23:55.944 align:middle line:84%
of course he was living
during the 18th century.

00:23:55.944 --> 00:23:56.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:23:56.610 --> 00:24:03.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: So it's something that
started in earnest, I believe,

00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:06.769 align:middle line:90%
in the 19th century--

00:24:06.769 --> 00:24:07.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:24:07.310 --> 00:24:09.010 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --and
early 20th century.

00:24:09.010 --> 00:24:11.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Again, we keep
going back to the same period.

00:24:11.510 --> 00:24:15.710 align:middle line:84%
Massive amounts of discoveries
just prior to that, and then

00:24:15.710 --> 00:24:19.770 align:middle line:84%
a seeming quashing of
the evidence after that,

00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:22.686 align:middle line:84%
following that, which
is the interesting.

00:24:22.686 --> 00:24:24.810 align:middle line:84%
And I know we did talk
about that in the last show.

00:24:24.810 --> 00:24:27.226 align:middle line:84%
What I would like to do also--
there were a couple others.

00:24:27.226 --> 00:24:30.270 align:middle line:84%
If you could get to
Sir Oliver Lodge?

00:24:30.270 --> 00:24:34.620 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Sir Oliver Lodge was
a prominent British physicist

00:24:34.620 --> 00:24:39.390 align:middle line:84%
who lived in the
early 20th century.

00:24:39.390 --> 00:24:43.400 align:middle line:90%
And he had a son named Raymond.

00:24:43.400 --> 00:24:48.400 align:middle line:84%
And his son Raymond
died during World War I.

00:24:48.400 --> 00:24:51.080 align:middle line:90%
He was in the British military.

00:24:51.080 --> 00:24:54.470 align:middle line:90%
He was killed in Europe.

00:24:54.470 --> 00:25:03.970 align:middle line:84%
So after that, Lodge
tried to establish contact

00:25:03.970 --> 00:25:07.570 align:middle line:90%
with the spirit of his son.

00:25:07.570 --> 00:25:10.980 align:middle line:90%
And he made use of a medium.

00:25:10.980 --> 00:25:15.800 align:middle line:90%
And he went in disguise.

00:25:15.800 --> 00:25:21.400 align:middle line:84%
And he didn't let the
medium know who he was.

00:25:21.400 --> 00:25:27.190 align:middle line:84%
And through the interactions
with this medium,

00:25:27.190 --> 00:25:33.530 align:middle line:84%
he got communications
from a conscious entity

00:25:33.530 --> 00:25:36.730 align:middle line:84%
that revealed things
that would only

00:25:36.730 --> 00:25:40.860 align:middle line:84%
have been known to his
son, very intimate details

00:25:40.860 --> 00:25:46.570 align:middle line:84%
about the family history and his
personal dealings with his son.

00:25:46.570 --> 00:25:55.290 align:middle line:84%
So what I find interesting is
that Lodge published a book

00:25:55.290 --> 00:25:58.490 align:middle line:90%
about this whole case.

00:25:58.490 --> 00:26:01.030 align:middle line:84%
And in it, he dealt
with a lot of the types

00:26:01.030 --> 00:26:03.220 align:middle line:84%
of skeptical
objections that might

00:26:03.220 --> 00:26:09.310 align:middle line:84%
be made by some of his
scientific colleagues.

00:26:09.310 --> 00:26:14.330 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's a
really good example

00:26:14.330 --> 00:26:17.320 align:middle line:84%
of a prominent
physicist who came

00:26:17.320 --> 00:26:23.010 align:middle line:84%
to accept that
consciousness can survive

00:26:23.010 --> 00:26:25.087 align:middle line:90%
the death of the physical body.

00:26:25.087 --> 00:26:25.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:26:25.670 --> 00:26:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And this is something
I'm absolutely convinced of--

00:26:28.180 --> 00:26:28.763 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:26:28.763 --> 00:26:33.190 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --that this body is
a vehicle for a conscious self

00:26:33.190 --> 00:26:37.760 align:middle line:90%
that has a non-material source.

00:26:37.760 --> 00:26:40.600 align:middle line:84%
Now, this idea is not
very popular in the world

00:26:40.600 --> 00:26:42.240 align:middle line:90%
of science today.

00:26:42.240 --> 00:26:47.280 align:middle line:84%
The most common idea today
in the world of science

00:26:47.280 --> 00:26:50.480 align:middle line:84%
is that consciousness
is produced

00:26:50.480 --> 00:26:55.680 align:middle line:84%
by the interaction of
chemicals within the brain.

00:26:55.680 --> 00:26:58.470 align:middle line:84%
Most cognitive or
neuroscientists

00:26:58.470 --> 00:27:01.910 align:middle line:84%
would say if you organized
the molecules in the brain

00:27:01.910 --> 00:27:04.560 align:middle line:84%
in a sufficiently
complex way, they'll

00:27:04.560 --> 00:27:08.700 align:middle line:84%
generate consciousness,
but only temporarily

00:27:08.700 --> 00:27:11.041 align:middle line:90%
and only in association with--

00:27:11.041 --> 00:27:12.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: With
firings of the brain.

00:27:12.540 --> 00:27:13.714 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: --the firings-

00:27:13.714 --> 00:27:14.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:27:14.380 --> 00:27:16.120 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --of the
brain, which means

00:27:16.120 --> 00:27:19.880 align:middle line:84%
ultimately there is
no conscious self

00:27:19.880 --> 00:27:26.680 align:middle line:84%
that could survive the
demise of the physical body.

00:27:26.680 --> 00:27:29.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is interesting,
because it brings us

00:27:29.290 --> 00:27:33.180 align:middle line:84%
into the subject of this
dual nature of ourselves,

00:27:33.180 --> 00:27:35.520 align:middle line:84%
which you're saying in
your work is absolutely

00:27:35.520 --> 00:27:40.100 align:middle line:84%
essential to being able to
piece together-- utilizing

00:27:40.100 --> 00:27:42.410 align:middle line:84%
the non-physical aspect
of our intelligence

00:27:42.410 --> 00:27:45.330 align:middle line:84%
is essential in piecing
together our ancient history.

00:27:45.330 --> 00:27:47.540 align:middle line:84%
You can't do it just
looking for bones alone.

00:27:47.540 --> 00:27:50.270 align:middle line:90%
That's not sufficient.

00:27:50.270 --> 00:27:51.360 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Absolutely.

00:27:51.360 --> 00:27:55.920 align:middle line:84%
Now, what the stones
and bones show us

00:27:55.920 --> 00:27:59.554 align:middle line:84%
if we actually look at
all of the evidence--

00:27:59.554 --> 00:28:00.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:28:00.220 --> 00:28:04.410 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --is that
humans have been here

00:28:04.410 --> 00:28:10.010 align:middle line:84%
since the very beginning
of life on Earth.

00:28:10.010 --> 00:28:12.953 align:middle line:84%
When people read my book
"Forbidden Archeology,"--

00:28:12.953 --> 00:28:13.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:28:13.700 --> 00:28:14.987 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: --they noticed that.

00:28:14.987 --> 00:28:15.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:28:15.570 --> 00:28:17.730 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And now
what that means is

00:28:17.730 --> 00:28:23.510 align:middle line:84%
we need new explanations
for human origins.

00:28:23.510 --> 00:28:25.690 align:middle line:84%
So people would ask
me that question.

00:28:25.690 --> 00:28:32.450 align:middle line:84%
OK, what is your explanation
of how we came about?

00:28:32.450 --> 00:28:34.560 align:middle line:84%
And to answer that
question, I wrote

00:28:34.560 --> 00:28:36.140 align:middle line:84%
a book called
"Human Devolution."

00:28:36.140 --> 00:28:40.330 align:middle line:84%
And what I proposed
there was before we even

00:28:40.330 --> 00:28:45.590 align:middle line:84%
ask the question where did
human beings come from,

00:28:45.590 --> 00:28:50.950 align:middle line:84%
we should first of all ask the
question what is a human being?

00:28:50.950 --> 00:28:55.620 align:middle line:84%
Now, as I was just saying
today, most scientists

00:28:55.620 --> 00:28:58.910 align:middle line:84%
would say we're just
machines made of matter.

00:28:58.910 --> 00:29:03.160 align:middle line:84%
And as far as mind and
consciousness are concerned,

00:29:03.160 --> 00:29:06.780 align:middle line:84%
well, if you organize
matter in a very complex way

00:29:06.780 --> 00:29:12.230 align:middle line:84%
in the brain, the brain will
produce mind and consciousness.

00:29:12.230 --> 00:29:17.520 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very materialistic
conception of who we are.

00:29:17.520 --> 00:29:18.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:29:18.210 --> 00:29:21.790 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: But what
I'm proposing is

00:29:21.790 --> 00:29:27.710 align:middle line:84%
that we're made of three things,
matter, the ordinary chemical

00:29:27.710 --> 00:29:28.360 align:middle line:90%
elements.

00:29:28.360 --> 00:29:31.250 align:middle line:90%
That's part of what we are.

00:29:31.250 --> 00:29:35.860 align:middle line:84%
But beyond that, there
is a subtle mind element

00:29:35.860 --> 00:29:41.875 align:middle line:84%
with some very unusual
powers like remote viewing--

00:29:41.875 --> 00:29:44.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which
everyone's capable of.

00:29:44.170 --> 00:29:44.760 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes.

00:29:44.760 --> 00:29:45.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Everyone.

00:29:45.060 --> 00:29:46.590 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And we could
talk about that.

00:29:46.590 --> 00:29:47.173 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:29:47.173 --> 00:29:49.030 align:middle line:90%
Well, yes.

00:29:49.030 --> 00:29:52.570 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And beyond that
subtle mind element,

00:29:52.570 --> 00:30:00.860 align:middle line:84%
there is a conscious self
which is totally non-material.

00:30:00.860 --> 00:30:04.210 align:middle line:84%
Now, when I'm speaking about
mind and consciousness,

00:30:04.210 --> 00:30:07.084 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean
temporary byproducts--

00:30:07.084 --> 00:30:07.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:30:07.750 --> 00:30:09.620 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: --of brain chemistry.

00:30:09.620 --> 00:30:14.766 align:middle line:84%
I mean real things with their
own independent existence.

00:30:14.766 --> 00:30:15.953 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:30:15.953 --> 00:30:16.900 align:middle line:90%
Subtle bodies.

00:30:16.900 --> 00:30:17.720 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Right.

00:30:17.720 --> 00:30:22.330 align:middle line:84%
So if we're going to
explain where we came from,

00:30:22.330 --> 00:30:26.010 align:middle line:84%
we have to explain, well,
where does that consciousness

00:30:26.010 --> 00:30:27.250 align:middle line:90%
come from?

00:30:27.250 --> 00:30:29.190 align:middle line:90%
Where does the matter come from?

00:30:29.190 --> 00:30:33.670 align:middle line:84%
How do they all come
together in the human form

00:30:33.670 --> 00:30:37.810 align:middle line:84%
as we experience
it on this Earth?

00:30:37.810 --> 00:30:41.150 align:middle line:84%
So what I'm proposing is
that originally, we're

00:30:41.150 --> 00:30:43.020 align:middle line:90%
beings of pure conscience.

00:30:43.020 --> 00:30:45.160 align:middle line:90%
That's what we are.

00:30:45.160 --> 00:30:49.570 align:middle line:84%
We originally exist in
harmony with all other beings

00:30:49.570 --> 00:30:54.030 align:middle line:84%
of pure consciousness and the
source of all conscious beings.

00:30:54.030 --> 00:31:02.150 align:middle line:84%
But if a conscious self
leaves that original state,

00:31:02.150 --> 00:31:08.250 align:middle line:84%
then it becomes
associated with matter.

00:31:08.250 --> 00:31:12.150 align:middle line:84%
It comes down into
lower levels of reality.

00:31:12.150 --> 00:31:15.160 align:middle line:90%
And why is that?

00:31:15.160 --> 00:31:18.930 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's because that original
level of pure consciousness

00:31:18.930 --> 00:31:22.880 align:middle line:84%
is based on love,
unselfish love.

00:31:22.880 --> 00:31:27.295 align:middle line:84%
If a conscious self becomes
exploitative or selfish,

00:31:27.295 --> 00:31:31.580 align:middle line:84%
it could no longer
exist in that harmony.

00:31:31.580 --> 00:31:34.335 align:middle line:84%
It needs a field
of activities where

00:31:34.335 --> 00:31:41.390 align:middle line:84%
it can act out its desires to
control, dominate, and exploit

00:31:41.390 --> 00:31:43.320 align:middle line:90%
matter and others.

00:31:43.320 --> 00:31:45.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In these denser
physical frequencies

00:31:45.550 --> 00:31:46.240 align:middle line:90%
or realities.

00:31:46.240 --> 00:31:47.390 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes.

00:31:47.390 --> 00:31:48.880 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:31:48.880 --> 00:31:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And for that purpose,
it needs a vehicle.

00:31:52.510 --> 00:31:55.960 align:middle line:84%
And there are different
kinds of vehicles.

00:31:55.960 --> 00:31:57.560 align:middle line:90%
There are human vehicles.

00:31:57.560 --> 00:31:59.290 align:middle line:90%
They are plant vehicles.

00:31:59.290 --> 00:32:02.010 align:middle line:90%
There are animal vehicles.

00:32:02.010 --> 00:32:06.560 align:middle line:84%
According to the state
of consciousness,

00:32:06.560 --> 00:32:11.040 align:middle line:84%
it is placed in a
certain vehicle.

00:32:11.040 --> 00:32:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And where do those
vehicles come from?

00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:15.912 align:middle line:84%
Well, it comes from higher
intelligences in the cosmos.

00:32:15.912 --> 00:32:17.370 align:middle line:10%
>>CREMO: And it's
worth bringing up

00:32:17.370 --> 00:32:19.930 align:middle line:10%
at this point, I think, the
point, because it struck me

00:32:19.930 --> 00:32:23.290 align:middle line:10%
in your book, that the
co-founder of the theory

00:32:23.290 --> 00:32:25.120 align:middle line:10%
of evolution with
Darwin-- I mean,

00:32:25.120 --> 00:32:27.450 align:middle line:10%
the way it was ultimately
played out politically,

00:32:27.450 --> 00:32:31.710 align:middle line:10%
Wallace-- actually
came to believe

00:32:31.710 --> 00:32:33.030 align:middle line:10%
there is an evolution of sorts.

00:32:33.030 --> 00:32:35.080 align:middle line:84%
But it's guided by a
higher intelligence, which

00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:37.400 align:middle line:84%
has come to be, as we were
saying off camera, kind

00:32:37.400 --> 00:32:39.960 align:middle line:84%
of a fusion between
science and religion,

00:32:39.960 --> 00:32:43.309 align:middle line:84%
so that it can live peacefully
together at this point in time.

00:32:43.309 --> 00:32:43.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes.

00:32:43.850 --> 00:32:48.105 align:middle line:84%
I think Wallace was an
excellent example of that.

00:32:48.105 --> 00:32:48.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:32:48.730 --> 00:32:50.710 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: He was
able to integrate

00:32:50.710 --> 00:32:53.390 align:middle line:84%
his spirituality
and his science.

00:32:53.390 --> 00:32:58.920 align:middle line:84%
And the result is a more
complete and better science.

00:32:58.920 --> 00:33:00.436 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:33:00.436 --> 00:33:02.820 align:middle line:84%
And right now,
they're saying, well,

00:33:02.820 --> 00:33:04.100 align:middle line:90%
show me the physical evidence.

00:33:04.100 --> 00:33:07.150 align:middle line:84%
So along that line, we
have a few little pieces

00:33:07.150 --> 00:33:08.400 align:middle line:90%
that we can talk about.

00:33:08.400 --> 00:33:10.480 align:middle line:84%
I just took a few
excerpts from your book

00:33:10.480 --> 00:33:13.930 align:middle line:84%
just to drive home the point
that these bones exist.

00:33:13.930 --> 00:33:16.140 align:middle line:90%
This isn't theory.

00:33:16.140 --> 00:33:18.860 align:middle line:84%
One of them I found
intriguing, because it's not

00:33:18.860 --> 00:33:22.620 align:middle line:84%
far from where I live actually,
is in the California Gold Rush

00:33:22.620 --> 00:33:25.930 align:middle line:84%
territory, Table Mountain,
that particular discovery.

00:33:25.930 --> 00:33:29.070 align:middle line:84%
If you could talk about that a
bit, because that's quite old.

00:33:29.070 --> 00:33:33.740 align:middle line:10%
>>CREMO: That is a
really fascinating case.

00:33:33.740 --> 00:33:36.535 align:middle line:10%
As I say, my work starts
with the stones and bones.

00:33:36.535 --> 00:33:37.160 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:33:37.160 --> 00:33:39.485 align:middle line:10%
>>CREMO: But from there,
it goes on to other things.

00:33:39.485 --> 00:33:40.360 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:33:40.360 --> 00:33:41.970 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: But an
important first step--

00:33:41.970 --> 00:33:43.178 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So in the trenches.

00:33:43.178 --> 00:33:45.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --in getting there from
the scientific point of view

00:33:45.960 --> 00:33:48.390 align:middle line:84%
is showing there
is evidence that

00:33:48.390 --> 00:33:52.150 align:middle line:84%
contradicts the current
theories of human origins.

00:33:52.150 --> 00:33:55.760 align:middle line:84%
Now, in the mid-19th
century, gold

00:33:55.760 --> 00:33:58.470 align:middle line:90%
was discovered in California.

00:33:58.470 --> 00:34:01.200 align:middle line:84%
And to get the gold,
miners came to places

00:34:01.200 --> 00:34:05.237 align:middle line:84%
like Table Mountain,
which is near Sonora in--

00:34:05.237 --> 00:34:06.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Tuolumne County.

00:34:06.320 --> 00:34:09.929 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --Tuolumne County in
the Sierra Nevada Mountains.

00:34:09.929 --> 00:34:13.550 align:middle line:84%
And they were digging tunnels
into the sides of that mountain

00:34:13.550 --> 00:34:15.560 align:middle line:90%
to get the gold.

00:34:15.560 --> 00:34:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And deep inside the
tunnels in the solid rock,

00:34:19.770 --> 00:34:24.489 align:middle line:84%
the miners found human
bones and human artifacts.

00:34:24.489 --> 00:34:27.949 align:middle line:84%
They found stone
mortars and pestles.

00:34:27.949 --> 00:34:30.429 align:middle line:84%
They found obsidian
spear points.

00:34:30.429 --> 00:34:33.780 align:middle line:84%
They found human
bones and teeth.

00:34:33.780 --> 00:34:40.449 align:middle line:84%
These objects were collected
by Dr. J.D. Whitney, who

00:34:40.449 --> 00:34:44.800 align:middle line:84%
was the chief government
geologist of California.

00:34:44.800 --> 00:34:47.090 align:middle line:84%
Mount Whitney is
named after him.

00:34:47.090 --> 00:34:50.110 align:middle line:84%
He was a very
prominent scientist.

00:34:50.110 --> 00:34:54.690 align:middle line:84%
And he reported
these discoveries

00:34:54.690 --> 00:34:55.690 align:middle line:90%
to the scientific world.

00:34:55.690 --> 00:34:58.470 align:middle line:84%
Now, what makes them
really significant

00:34:58.470 --> 00:35:02.450 align:middle line:84%
is they're found in
layers of solid rock

00:35:02.450 --> 00:35:10.750 align:middle line:84%
that modern geologists tell us
are about 50 million years old,

00:35:10.750 --> 00:35:12.730 align:middle line:84%
which is really
quite extraordinary

00:35:12.730 --> 00:35:18.270 align:middle line:84%
because the dominant idea today
is that humans like us came

00:35:18.270 --> 00:35:22.610 align:middle line:84%
into existence less
than 200,000 years ago.

00:35:22.610 --> 00:35:26.730 align:middle line:84%
So to have this evidence
showing that humans

00:35:26.730 --> 00:35:31.810 align:middle line:84%
like us were present
50 million years ago

00:35:31.810 --> 00:35:33.864 align:middle line:90%
is really quite astonishing.

00:35:33.864 --> 00:35:36.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're still looking
for Native American Indian

00:35:36.280 --> 00:35:40.390 align:middle line:84%
arrowheads as evidence of
our antiquity from a couple

00:35:40.390 --> 00:35:42.367 align:middle line:90%
hundred years ago.

00:35:42.367 --> 00:35:42.950 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:35:42.950 --> 00:35:48.910 align:middle line:84%
And this discovery, as
announced by Dr. Whitney,

00:35:48.910 --> 00:35:52.230 align:middle line:90%
created some controversy.

00:35:52.230 --> 00:35:56.740 align:middle line:84%
And the scientific
community basically

00:35:56.740 --> 00:35:59.760 align:middle line:90%
rejected the discoveries.

00:35:59.760 --> 00:36:03.430 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting
why they rejected it.

00:36:03.430 --> 00:36:07.060 align:middle line:84%
There was an anthropologist
named William Holmes, who

00:36:07.060 --> 00:36:14.540 align:middle line:84%
worked at the Smithsonian
Institution in Washington DC.

00:36:14.540 --> 00:36:18.070 align:middle line:84%
And he wrote in
one of his reports,

00:36:18.070 --> 00:36:23.800 align:middle line:84%
if Dr. Whitney had understood
the theory of human evolution,

00:36:23.800 --> 00:36:26.910 align:middle line:84%
he wouldn't have come
to those conclusions.

00:36:26.910 --> 00:36:30.850 align:middle line:84%
And in other words,
if the facts didn't

00:36:30.850 --> 00:36:34.760 align:middle line:84%
support the theory of
evolution with its ideas

00:36:34.760 --> 00:36:38.230 align:middle line:84%
of a recent origin
for the human species,

00:36:38.230 --> 00:36:40.390 align:middle line:84%
he shouldn't have
published that report.

00:36:40.390 --> 00:36:45.330 align:middle line:84%
He should've known these things
could not possibly be true.

00:36:45.330 --> 00:36:49.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, many people think that the
way scientists should operate

00:36:49.990 --> 00:36:55.770 align:middle line:84%
is that if facts are discovered
that contradict a theory,

00:36:55.770 --> 00:36:59.580 align:middle line:84%
the theory should be modified
to accommodate the facts.

00:36:59.580 --> 00:37:03.780 align:middle line:84%
But that's not the way
that it always works.

00:37:03.780 --> 00:37:07.340 align:middle line:84%
And in this case, it
most certainly wasn't.

00:37:07.340 --> 00:37:12.400 align:middle line:84%
So according to Holmes,
these discoveries

00:37:12.400 --> 00:37:13.679 align:middle line:90%
should not have been reported.

00:37:13.679 --> 00:37:14.345 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:37:14.345 --> 00:37:16.470 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: They should have
simply been forgotten.

00:37:16.470 --> 00:37:19.300 align:middle line:84%
And basically,
that's what happened.

00:37:19.300 --> 00:37:21.840 align:middle line:84%
Now Whitney, he
published this report.

00:37:21.840 --> 00:37:27.190 align:middle line:84%
It was published by Harvard
University in the year in 1880.

00:37:27.190 --> 00:37:31.930 align:middle line:84%
But we don't read about
these things in the textbooks

00:37:31.930 --> 00:37:39.130 align:middle line:84%
today, because of what I call a
process of knowledge filtration

00:37:39.130 --> 00:37:42.510 align:middle line:84%
that operates in the
world of science.

00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:45.960 align:middle line:84%
Now, some of those
artifacts are still

00:37:45.960 --> 00:37:49.850 align:middle line:84%
in the collection of the
Museum of Anthropology

00:37:49.850 --> 00:37:53.740 align:middle line:84%
at the University of
California at Berkeley.

00:37:53.740 --> 00:37:54.980 align:middle line:90%
And I've been there.

00:37:54.980 --> 00:37:56.660 align:middle line:90%
I've seen them.

00:37:56.660 --> 00:38:00.760 align:middle line:84%
But the average person
who goes to the museum

00:38:00.760 --> 00:38:03.230 align:middle line:84%
would not suspect that
those things are there.

00:38:03.230 --> 00:38:06.380 align:middle line:90%
They're not shown to the public.

00:38:06.380 --> 00:38:10.810 align:middle line:84%
The average person would have
no idea that they're there.

00:38:10.810 --> 00:38:13.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And what about-- there
was also something in Kentucky

00:38:13.760 --> 00:38:16.081 align:middle line:84%
that harks back to about
300 million years ago.

00:38:16.081 --> 00:38:18.580 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's the same as
what we talked about earlier.

00:38:18.580 --> 00:38:21.380 align:middle line:84%
Wasn't it human
footprints they found?

00:38:21.380 --> 00:38:23.050 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yes.

00:38:23.050 --> 00:38:27.710 align:middle line:84%
There was a scientist
working in Kentucky

00:38:27.710 --> 00:38:33.560 align:middle line:84%
in the 1930s and
1940s who reported

00:38:33.560 --> 00:38:39.270 align:middle line:84%
the existence of
human footprints

00:38:39.270 --> 00:38:46.440 align:middle line:84%
in sedimentary formations
about 300 million years old

00:38:46.440 --> 00:38:48.030 align:middle line:90%
in Kentucky.

00:38:48.030 --> 00:38:50.640 align:middle line:84%
Now, some of the
skeptics said, well,

00:38:50.640 --> 00:38:54.570 align:middle line:84%
these must've been carved
into the rock somehow.

00:38:54.570 --> 00:38:56.920 align:middle line:84%
But he did detailed
studies, and he

00:38:56.920 --> 00:39:04.010 align:middle line:84%
showed that-- he did
microphotographic studies that

00:39:04.010 --> 00:39:10.010 align:middle line:84%
examined the grains
of sand in this rock.

00:39:10.010 --> 00:39:13.160 align:middle line:84%
And it showed that
there was compression.

00:39:13.160 --> 00:39:16.120 align:middle line:84%
In other words, that
the grains of sand

00:39:16.120 --> 00:39:20.240 align:middle line:84%
at the bottom of the footprints
were compressed together more

00:39:20.240 --> 00:39:26.340 align:middle line:84%
than the grains
of sand at the top

00:39:26.340 --> 00:39:28.280 align:middle line:84%
of the sides of the
footprint, which

00:39:28.280 --> 00:39:30.064 align:middle line:84%
indicated they were
made by pressure--

00:39:30.064 --> 00:39:30.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:39:30.730 --> 00:39:35.860 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: --not by
carving into the rock.

00:39:35.860 --> 00:39:38.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, some-- one of the
skeptical scientists

00:39:38.970 --> 00:39:40.510 align:middle line:84%
reported in a
scientific journal.

00:39:40.510 --> 00:39:45.460 align:middle line:84%
It says, if this
is true, then we

00:39:45.460 --> 00:39:48.200 align:middle line:84%
should give up our
professions as scientists

00:39:48.200 --> 00:39:50.255 align:middle line:84%
and all take jobs
as truck drivers.

00:39:50.255 --> 00:39:50.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:39:50.880 --> 00:39:53.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, sometimes that
might've been a good idea.

00:39:53.120 --> 00:39:54.420 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:39:54.420 --> 00:39:55.730 align:middle line:90%
It might have been.

00:39:55.730 --> 00:39:59.290 align:middle line:84%
But yes, that's another case
of archaeological evidence

00:39:59.290 --> 00:40:00.930 align:middle line:90%
for extreme human antiquity.

00:40:00.930 --> 00:40:04.730 align:middle line:84%
And here, we're looking at that
300 million year mark again,

00:40:04.730 --> 00:40:07.730 align:middle line:84%
same as the two instances
we talked about earlier on.

00:40:07.730 --> 00:40:10.420 align:middle line:84%
Let's do the reverse of what I
asked you the first time, which

00:40:10.420 --> 00:40:13.130 align:middle line:84%
is what was the modern
scientific view of what

00:40:13.130 --> 00:40:15.380 align:middle line:84%
was happening on the Earth
300 million years ago.

00:40:15.380 --> 00:40:16.680 align:middle line:90%
Now, you already answered that.

00:40:16.680 --> 00:40:19.260 align:middle line:84%
Now, let's look at what was
