00:42:19.696 --> 00:42:21.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is now
taking us back billions

00:42:21.570 --> 00:42:22.660 align:middle line:84%
and billions and
billions of years.

00:42:22.660 --> 00:42:24.450 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Hundreds of
millions of years.

00:42:24.450 --> 00:42:24.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:42:24.820 --> 00:42:26.300 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: Hundreds of
millions of years.

00:42:26.300 --> 00:42:27.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And even billions.

00:42:27.140 --> 00:42:27.723 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Yeah.

00:42:27.723 --> 00:42:28.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And here we go.

00:42:28.810 --> 00:42:32.800 align:middle line:84%
So the other number
that keeps coming up--

00:42:32.800 --> 00:42:36.300 align:middle line:84%
and I saw this repeatedly, I've
only pulled one example of it,

00:42:36.300 --> 00:42:40.310 align:middle line:84%
the Moulin Quignon jaw,
but it came up repeatedly

00:42:40.310 --> 00:42:44.960 align:middle line:84%
in your book-- was a period
of roughly 400,000 years ago.

00:42:44.960 --> 00:42:46.800 align:middle line:84%
It seems like a
lot of discoveries

00:42:46.800 --> 00:42:50.960 align:middle line:84%
have taken place that have
unearthed remnants of humans

00:42:50.960 --> 00:42:53.807 align:middle line:90%
from 400,000 years ago as well.

00:42:53.807 --> 00:42:54.640 align:middle line:90%
>>CREMO: Absolutely.

00:42:54.640 --> 00:42:58.700 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of discoveries
that date back to that period

00:42:58.700 --> 00:43:02.580 align:middle line:84%
between 300,00 and
400,000 years ago.

00:43:02.580 --> 00:43:05.050 align:middle line:84%
The Moulin Quignon
jaw is one of them.

00:43:05.050 --> 00:43:07.890 align:middle line:84%
That was a discovery
that was made

00:43:07.890 --> 00:43:12.340 align:middle line:84%
in the 19th century
in France by one

00:43:12.340 --> 00:43:18.370 align:middle line:84%
of the founders of modern
archaeology, Jacques Boucher de

00:43:18.370 --> 00:43:19.970 align:middle line:90%
Perthes.

00:43:19.970 --> 00:43:24.330 align:middle line:84%
And he had been
conducting excavations

00:43:24.330 --> 00:43:28.930 align:middle line:84%
in the Somme River Valley
in Northeastern France.

00:43:28.930 --> 00:43:30.570 align:middle line:84%
And at this place,
Moulin Quignon,

00:43:30.570 --> 00:43:38.350 align:middle line:84%
he uncovered an anatomically
modern human jaw in a formation

00:43:38.350 --> 00:43:46.900 align:middle line:84%
that modern geologists tell
us is over 400,000 years old.

00:43:46.900 --> 00:43:50.740 align:middle line:84%
Now, in the same
formation, he also

00:43:50.740 --> 00:43:53.450 align:middle line:84%
found many stone
tools and weapons.

00:43:53.450 --> 00:43:57.560 align:middle line:84%
But many scientists
of that time could not

00:43:57.560 --> 00:44:04.740 align:middle line:84%
accept that humans existed
so far in the past.

00:44:04.740 --> 00:44:07.340 align:middle line:90%
So what they proposed was this.

00:44:07.340 --> 00:44:12.860 align:middle line:84%
Somebody must have gone
to some Roman cemetery

00:44:12.860 --> 00:44:17.750 align:middle line:84%
and taken a human jawbone
maybe 2,000 years old,

00:44:17.750 --> 00:44:22.500 align:middle line:84%
and then planted it in the
excavation for Boucher de

00:44:22.500 --> 00:44:24.200 align:middle line:90%
Perthes to find.

00:44:24.200 --> 00:44:27.590 align:middle line:84%
And actually, that's the
explanation for this discovery

00:44:27.590 --> 00:44:30.530 align:middle line:84%
that you see in the
modern textbooks.

00:44:30.530 --> 00:44:35.420 align:middle line:84%
What you don't see in
the modern textbooks

00:44:35.420 --> 00:44:39.760 align:middle line:84%
is that after he heard
these accusations,

00:44:39.760 --> 00:44:44.210 align:middle line:84%
Boucher de Perthes made
additional excavations

00:44:44.210 --> 00:44:49.100 align:middle line:84%
into the same formations under
conditions that completely

00:44:49.100 --> 00:44:54.240 align:middle line:90%
ruled out this hoax hypothesis.

00:44:54.240 --> 00:44:56.840 align:middle line:84%
The new excavations
were witnessed

00:44:56.840 --> 00:44:59.550 align:middle line:84%
by other professionals,
scientists.

00:44:59.550 --> 00:45:03.970 align:middle line:84%
And in these new
excavations, he excavated

00:45:03.970 --> 00:45:09.970 align:middle line:84%
100 additional anatomically
modern human bones and teeth

00:45:09.970 --> 00:45:12.380 align:middle line:90%
from the same formations.

00:45:12.380 --> 00:45:15.980 align:middle line:84%
And I think they
verify the reality

00:45:15.980 --> 00:45:19.150 align:middle line:84%
of the original discovery
of the human jaw he

00:45:19.150 --> 00:45:21.240 align:middle line:90%
found in those formations.

00:45:21.240 --> 00:45:25.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is a discovery
from the 19th century.

00:45:25.440 --> 00:45:27.750 align:middle line:84%
Now, some people
might wonder, well,

00:45:27.750 --> 00:45:31.140 align:middle line:84%
what about the 20th
century, more recent times.

00:45:31.140 --> 00:45:34.500 align:middle line:84%
There have been discoveries
from that same period,

00:45:34.500 --> 00:45:37.780 align:middle line:84%
between 300,000
and 400,000 years,

00:45:37.780 --> 00:45:39.780 align:middle line:90%
from more modern scientists.

00:45:39.780 --> 00:45:42.020 align:middle line:10%
Virginia Steen-McIntyre,
for example,

00:45:42.020 --> 00:45:44.650 align:middle line:10%
is an American geologist.

00:45:44.650 --> 00:45:48.650 align:middle line:10%
She was called down
to Mexico to date

00:45:48.650 --> 00:45:53.580 align:middle line:10%
an archaeological site at
a place called Hueyatlaco.

00:45:53.580 --> 00:45:55.890 align:middle line:84%
Some American
archaeologists there

00:45:55.890 --> 00:46:00.810 align:middle line:84%
had uncovered human artifacts,
stone tools and weapons.

00:46:00.810 --> 00:46:03.450 align:middle line:84%
And they wanted to
know how old they were.

00:46:03.450 --> 00:46:07.220 align:middle line:84%
So Virginia Steen-McIntyre
and her colleagues

00:46:07.220 --> 00:46:09.390 align:middle line:90%
went to that place.

00:46:09.390 --> 00:46:15.490 align:middle line:84%
And they used four scientific
methods to date the site.

00:46:15.490 --> 00:46:20.640 align:middle line:84%
And they concluded the
site must be at least

00:46:20.640 --> 00:46:24.990 align:middle line:90%
250,000 or 300,000 years old.

00:46:24.990 --> 00:46:28.480 align:middle line:84%
But the archaeologists
couldn't accept that.

00:46:28.480 --> 00:46:33.280 align:middle line:84%
They said human beings capable
of making these things did not

00:46:33.280 --> 00:46:38.130 align:middle line:84%
exist anywhere in the world
at that period of time,

00:46:38.130 --> 00:46:42.650 align:middle line:84%
and what to speak of being
present in North America.

00:46:42.650 --> 00:46:45.980 align:middle line:84%
The current scientific
idea is that there

00:46:45.980 --> 00:46:47.990 align:middle line:84%
are no human beings
in North America

00:46:47.990 --> 00:46:52.210 align:middle line:84%
any earlier than about
20,000 years ago.

00:46:52.210 --> 00:46:53.585 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And here
you're finding

00:46:53.585 --> 00:46:55.270 align:middle line:90%
evidence 300 million years old.

