00:51:25.570 --> 00:51:30.570 align:middle line:84%
I'm just back from a meeting
of the World Archaeological

00:51:30.570 --> 00:51:36.910 align:middle line:84%
Congress that was held on
the Dead Sea in Jordan.

00:51:36.910 --> 00:51:39.790 align:middle line:84%
And it's one of
the world's largest

00:51:39.790 --> 00:51:43.190 align:middle line:84%
international organizations
of archaeologists.

00:51:43.190 --> 00:51:47.880 align:middle line:84%
They meet every four years
in a different country.

00:51:47.880 --> 00:51:52.380 align:middle line:84%
So at this most recent
meeting, I presented a paper.

00:51:52.380 --> 00:51:56.300 align:middle line:84%
And I chose to present
a paper about how

00:51:56.300 --> 00:51:59.650 align:middle line:84%
a prominent
scientist, John Talbot

00:51:59.650 --> 00:52:05.900 align:middle line:84%
Robinson, famous for his
discoveries of the ape man

00:52:05.900 --> 00:52:09.300 align:middle line:84%
Australopithecus
in South Africa,

00:52:09.300 --> 00:52:15.400 align:middle line:84%
used a theosophist
psychic in his work

00:52:15.400 --> 00:52:22.540 align:middle line:84%
at the Sterkfontein cave
site in South Africa.

00:52:22.540 --> 00:52:24.260 align:middle line:90%
It's interesting what happened.

00:52:24.260 --> 00:52:27.880 align:middle line:84%
You know, he had
met this psychic

00:52:27.880 --> 00:52:32.240 align:middle line:90%
through a contact of his.

00:52:32.240 --> 00:52:35.910 align:middle line:84%
And he thought he might be
helpful for his research.

00:52:35.910 --> 00:52:39.550 align:middle line:84%
So he brought him to
the Sterkfontein caves.

00:52:39.550 --> 00:52:46.340 align:middle line:84%
And this man laid down there
and went into a yogic trance.

00:52:46.340 --> 00:52:52.720 align:middle line:84%
And Robinson would put a
fossil on his forehead,

00:52:52.720 --> 00:52:57.370 align:middle line:84%
for example, a tooth
of Australopithecus.

00:52:57.370 --> 00:53:01.980 align:middle line:84%
And this psychic,
this clairvoyant,

00:53:01.980 --> 00:53:07.430 align:middle line:84%
would be able to see the
whole creature and what

00:53:07.430 --> 00:53:11.270 align:middle line:84%
it was doing millions
of years ago.

00:53:11.270 --> 00:53:15.850 align:middle line:84%
And there were five sessions
like this that took place

00:53:15.850 --> 00:53:18.420 align:middle line:84%
on separate days
on different days

00:53:18.420 --> 00:53:23.030 align:middle line:84%
in the Sterkfontein caves
involving dozens of fossils

00:53:23.030 --> 00:53:27.150 align:middle line:84%
of many different
species of ape men.

00:53:27.150 --> 00:53:31.780 align:middle line:84%
And he was able to
report correctly

00:53:31.780 --> 00:53:39.410 align:middle line:84%
the anatomical details of these
creatures and their behavior.

00:53:39.410 --> 00:53:43.830 align:middle line:84%
And it helped Robinson
and his research.

00:53:43.830 --> 00:53:48.880 align:middle line:84%
So I thought it was
important for archaeologists

00:53:48.880 --> 00:53:54.980 align:middle line:84%
to understand that there are
different ways for getting

00:53:54.980 --> 00:53:57.620 align:middle line:90%
knowledge of the past.

00:53:57.620 --> 00:54:01.670 align:middle line:84%
I mean, one way is
to just take a fossil

00:54:01.670 --> 00:54:05.450 align:middle line:84%
and study it with different
radiometric dating methods

00:54:05.450 --> 00:54:10.010 align:middle line:84%
and chemical techniques
and physical measurements.

00:54:10.010 --> 00:54:13.920 align:middle line:84%
But I thought it was interesting
that a very prominent person,

00:54:13.920 --> 00:54:18.690 align:middle line:84%
a very prominent
scientist, had expanded

00:54:18.690 --> 00:54:24.340 align:middle line:84%
his way of doing things
to include a psychic.

00:54:24.340 --> 00:54:26.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think
it's totally valid.

00:54:26.070 --> 00:54:29.000 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: And there are
other archaeologists

00:54:29.000 --> 00:54:30.770 align:middle line:90%
who have also done that.

00:54:30.770 --> 00:54:33.330 align:middle line:84%
There was an
archaeologist in England

00:54:33.330 --> 00:54:39.230 align:middle line:84%
early in the 20th century
named Frederick Bligh Bond.

00:54:39.230 --> 00:54:44.590 align:middle line:84%
He was excavating the
Glastonbury Cathedral

00:54:44.590 --> 00:54:47.280 align:middle line:90%
in Glastonbury, England.

00:54:47.280 --> 00:54:51.860 align:middle line:84%
It had been destroyed during
the reign of King Henry

00:54:51.860 --> 00:54:57.410 align:middle line:84%
VIII in England
hundreds of years ago.

00:54:57.410 --> 00:55:03.280 align:middle line:84%
And he employed a psychic
who had the ability

00:55:03.280 --> 00:55:06.390 align:middle line:84%
to communicate with
past intelligences

00:55:06.390 --> 00:55:08.874 align:middle line:84%
by a technique called
automatic writing.

00:55:08.874 --> 00:55:09.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:55:09.540 --> 00:55:11.331 align:middle line:84%
>>CREMO: In other words,
